message:
Running command: python3 - << 'PY'
import random,subprocess,sys

def run_one(N,arr):
    inp = str(N)+"\n"+" ".join(map(str,arr))+"\n"
    p = subprocess.run(["python3","solution.py"], input=inp.encode(), stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE)
    out = p.stdout.decode().strip()
    expected = " ".join(str(sum(arr[i*7:(i+1)*7])) for i in range(N))
    return out, expected, p.returncode, p.stderr.decode()

for t in range(100):
    N=random.randint(1,10)
    arr=[random.randint(0,10**5) for _ in range(7*N)]
    out,expected,rc,err = run_one(N,arr)
    if out!=expected:
        print("FAIL",t,N)
        print("inp:", N, arr[:10], "...")
        print("out:",out)
        print("exp:",expected)
        sys.exit(2)
print("All tests passed")
